        <updateDate>2020-10-13T15:44:55Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Safe Indoor Spaces Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to establish a prize competition to incentivize the development of systems or devices that limit indoor transmission of COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) and the virus that causes it.</p> <p>To be eligible for the prize, a system or device must meet certain criteria with respect to decreased viral transmission rates, scalability, and costs.</p> <p>In addition, HHS must establish a board comprised of experts in public health, education, small business, and engineering to advise on this competition.</p> <p> <br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
